label: @ATMDIALOGFROMDATE
description: This variable prompts you for the oldest date of the ATM Dialog files that your specfile reads. If you set it to --/--/-- (Date Null), your specfile starts with the oldest ATM Dialog file available. The default value of this variable is --/--/--.

label: @ATMDIALOGTODATE
description: This variable prompts you for the newest date of the ATM Dialog files that your specfile reads. If you set it to --/--/-- (Date Null), your specfile ends with the newest ATM Dialog file available. The default value of this variable is --/--/--.
